Another controversy in the 2000 Olympics was that the women's all-around gold medal winner, Andreea Raducan of Romania, was stripped of her title after a banned substance was detected in a blood test. Despite her claims that this was from a cold medicine given to her by a team doctor, she had to return her medal and teammate Simona Amanar was named champion.